def: Belief in the existence of two gods; dualism.
A ganoid fish having rhombic enameled scales; one of theRhomboganoidei.
Being out of date; antiquated. [Obs.] Hammond.
A mineral occurring in hexagonal crystals, also massive,generally of a yellow color, containing silica, alumina, lime, soda,and carbon dioxide.
A spectro-electric tube in which the decomposition of a liquidby the passage of an electric spark is observed. Knight.
An instrument devised by Hermann, for regulating and measuringthe thickness of a layer of blood for spectroscopic examination.
To confine in, or as in, a cage; to coop up. [Written alsoencage.] "Incaged birds." Shak.
The quality or state of being stately.For stateliness and majesty, what is comparable to a horse Dr. H.More.
An instrument with a graduated disk by means of which theangles of gems are measured in the process of cutting and polishing.
The quality of being debonair; good humor; gentleness;courtesy. Sterne.
A mineral related to the micas, but low in silica and yieldingbrittle folia with pearly luster.
